<!--
  CLAUDE.md.template — a portable starter for the .claude/ infrastructure pattern.

  HOW TO USE
  1. Copy this file to your project root as CLAUDE.md and delete these comments.
  2. Create a .claude/ directory with the layers you need (see "The layers" below).
  3. Fill the sections. Keep CLAUDE.md short — it loads on EVERY session, so it
     should hold only what's true every time. Push detail into .claude/context/
     and let CLAUDE.md point at it.

  THE LAYERS (.claude/<layer>/) — least to most flexible, with hooks underneath:
    hooks/      Deterministic shell scripts the harness runs on lifecycle events.
                The model cannot skip them — the enforcement floor. Always-run
                things: formatting, branch guards, write protection, cache warming.
                Wired in .claude/settings.json.
    workflows/  Multi-step autonomous orchestrations (loop, branch, spawn agents).
    commands/   Single-shot prompt templates, invoked as /<name>. Stateless.
    agents/     Isolated subagents with clean context; return only summaries.
    skills/     Domain-expertise bundles (skills/<name>/SKILL.md) — how to think
                and behave for a task type.
    context/    Reference docs (schemas, API notes, stack briefs). CLAUDE.md points
                here; Claude deep-reads only what the task needs.

  COMPOSABILITY:  hooks underneath →  workflows ▸ commands ▸ agents ▸ skills
  Delete any layer you don't use. Don't fabricate content to fill the structure.
-->

